247
00:13:02,426 --> 00:13:04,726
-No! -What?

248
00:13:04,726 --> 00:13:06,426
This keyhole...

249
00:13:06,426 --> 00:13:07,726
Something's glowing.

250
00:13:07,726 --> 00:13:08,726
What?

251
00:13:11,226 --> 00:13:13,826
This is florescent paint.

252
00:13:13,826 --> 00:13:17,726
Inspector, there's florescent on the keyhole on this side too.

253
00:13:17,726 --> 00:13:18,826
Which means...

254
00:13:18,826 --> 00:13:20,726
No way!

255
00:13:20,726 --> 00:13:22,026
Just as I thought.

256
00:13:22,026 --> 00:13:25,726
There's florescent paint on the tip of all four keys.

257
00:13:25,726 --> 00:13:27,326
It probably got on there

258
00:13:27,326 --> 00:13:29,926
when the key was stuck into the keyhole.

259
00:13:29,926 --> 00:13:31,226
Which means, he was guided

260
00:13:31,226 --> 00:13:33,326
by the slightest light of the keyhole.

261
00:13:33,326 --> 00:13:34,626
Yes.

262
00:13:34,626 --> 00:13:36,926
He gave all his accomplices the keys in the dark

263
00:13:36,926 --> 00:13:38,826
and made them insert them into the glowing keyhole,

264
00:13:38,826 --> 00:13:40,126
then turn all the keys at the same time,

265
00:13:40,126 --> 00:13:46,026
then stole the horns of the giraffe, right?

