00:13:48,026 --> 00:13:50,726
What me?

268
00:13:50,726 --> 00:13:52,926
Isn't it so?

269
00:13:52,926 --> 00:13:55,526
It's an obvious fact that the keys

270
00:13:55,526 --> 00:13:59,126
that were used weren't spare keys but these keys.

271
00:13:59,126 --> 00:14:00,126
In other words,

272
00:14:00,126 --> 00:14:05,926
you nailed the keys on very lightly

273
00:14:05,926 --> 00:14:10,926
so that after using them you could put them back really easily.

274
00:14:10,926 --> 00:14:13,626
Then, try pulling that metal out.

275
00:14:13,626 --> 00:14:16,726
It won't come off that easily.

276
00:14:16,726 --> 00:14:20,726
You probably nailed it back firmly when you returned the keys.

277
00:14:20,726 --> 00:14:22,026
If you're going as far as to say that,

278
00:14:22,026 --> 00:14:24,426
why don't you check my body?

279
00:14:24,426 --> 00:14:26,426
If I'm Thief Kid, I should still have

280
00:14:26,426 --> 00:14:27,926
the horns of the giraffe on me.

281
00:14:27,926 --> 00:14:30,226
Yes, even if you don't tell me,

282
00:14:30,226 --> 00:14:31,326
that's exactly what I'm planning to do...

283
00:14:31,326 --> 00:14:32,726
Wait.

284
00:14:32,726 --> 00:14:36,026
Will you let us, the Youth Detective Squad

285
00:14:36,026 --> 00:14:38,826
do the body check?

286
00:14:38,826 --> 00:14:41,326
If you, Inspector or the advisor is Thief Kid

287
00:14:41,326 --> 00:14:43,226
and his accomplices,

288
00:14:43,226 --> 00:14:46,126
you may fake checking and deceive us.

289
00:14:46,126 --> 00:14:47,326
Exactly.

290
00:14:47,326 --> 00:14:49,126
We can be trusted.

291
00:14:49,126 --> 00:14:52,326
We're for sure not Thief Kid's accomplice.

292
00:14:52,326 --> 00:14:54,326
That's true.

293
00:14:54,326 --> 00:14:56,926
We'll be checking all the others too,

294
00:14:56,926 --> 00:14:58,526
but that's okay, right?

295
00:14:58,526 --> 00:14:59,526
Yes.

296
00:15:02,926 --> 00:15:06,826
"We will be making some changes in the program.

297
00:15:06,826 --> 00:15:09,526
Please wait a moment," it says.

298
00:15:09,526 --> 00:15:12,526
This telop has been streaming from some time ago.

299
00:15:12,526 --> 00:15:14,826
It's sure taking long for the program to restart.

300
00:15:14,826 --> 00:15:17,926
I wonder what that strange sound was, though?

301
00:15:17,926 --> 00:15:20,526
It was sure unpleasant to the ears.

302
00:15:20,526 --> 00:15:23,326
What? Was there such a sound?

303
00:15:29,226 --> 00:15:30,826
What?

304
00:15:30,826 --> 00:15:34,226
You checked all the people in this temple building

305
00:15:34,226 --> 00:15:37,226
but the giraffe's horn is nowhere in sight?

306
00:15:37,226 --> 00:15:41,226
No. We thought that maybe it may secretly

307
00:15:41,226 --> 00:15:42,726
have been put into our clothes and pockets too,

308
00:15:42,726 --> 00:15:44,126
so we checked our clothes

309
00:15:44,126 --> 00:15:46,726
as well as the pockets of Conan's clothes but couldn't find it.

310
00:15:46,726 --> 00:15:48,626
It's strange.

311
00:15:48,626 --> 00:15:50,326
The bars of the windows were made

312
00:15:50,326 --> 00:15:52,726
with a width that the giraffe's horn couldn't pass through,

313
00:15:52,726 --> 00:15:54,226
so even if his accomplices were to be outside,

314
00:15:54,226 --> 00:15:55,726
he couldn't have given it to them.

315
00:15:55,726 --> 00:15:57,826
That's why...

316
00:15:57,826 --> 00:16:00,326
Thief Kid's already fled.

317
00:16:00,326 --> 00:16:02,926
Open the door up right away so we can go after him.

318
00:16:02,926 --> 00:16:04,826
No, but...

319
00:16:04,826 --> 00:16:08,426
It's true. That since the treasure

320
00:16:08,426 --> 00:16:10,226
that he was after is no longer here,

321
00:16:10,226 --> 00:16:14,026
so it's most natural to think that he's gone,

322
00:16:14,026 --> 00:16:16,126
but I just don't get it.

323
00:16:16,126 --> 00:16:19,226
I wonder why he knocked Conan out.

324
00:16:19,226 --> 00:16:21,226
Well, I guess getting rid of the one

325
00:16:21,226 --> 00:16:22,326
who is thought to be most difficult to handle,

326
00:16:22,326 --> 00:16:25,126
would make things way easier,

327
00:16:25,126 --> 00:16:27,526
but doing so, would deprive Thief Kid of the pleasure

328
00:16:27,526 --> 00:16:29,626
of feeling superior for carrying out what he'd done

329
00:16:29,626 --> 00:16:31,626
right in front of Conan's eyes.

330
00:16:31,626 --> 00:16:35,326
I wonder if he had some other reason?

331
00:16:35,326 --> 00:16:37,226
And another thing that bothers me

332
00:16:37,226 --> 00:16:38,626
is this phrase written by Kichiemon Samizu

333
00:16:38,626 --> 00:16:41,026
that is carved on the pillar.

334
00:16:41,026 --> 00:16:43,026
"One who desires to acquire the giraffe

335
00:16:43,026 --> 00:16:45,126
without using the correct method,

336
00:16:45,126 --> 00:16:47,726
must move with the flow."

337
00:16:47,726 --> 00:16:51,026
In other words, it means,

338
00:16:51,026 --> 00:16:53,226
anyone who tries to acquire the giraffe's horn,

339
00:16:53,226 --> 00:16:55,726
not using the proper method, must go with the flow.

340
00:16:55,726 --> 00:16:59,926
The proper method probably refers to the keys,

341
00:16:59,926 --> 00:17:01,626
but what is the flow?

342
00:17:02,926 --> 00:17:04,426
Wind?

343
00:17:04,426 --> 00:17:06,426
The flow of the wind?

344
00:17:06,426 --> 00:17:09,126
No. The wind is blowing now

345
00:17:09,126 --> 00:17:11,426
because Thief Kid broke the shutters.

346
00:17:11,426 --> 00:17:13,826
That's right, why did Thief Kid open the window

347
00:17:13,826 --> 00:17:15,626
in the first place?

348
00:17:15,626 --> 00:17:17,126
He caused a black-out

349
00:17:17,126 --> 00:17:19,526
so it would've been meaningless for him to confuse us

350
00:17:19,526 --> 00:17:20,926
by bringing in the wind and rain.

351
00:17:21,926 --> 00:17:23,926
And, as Inspector Nakamori says,

352
00:17:23,926 --> 00:17:27,226
if Advisor Suzuki were to be Thief Kid,

353
00:17:27,226 --> 00:17:30,126
to take the keys that are fixed

354
00:17:30,126 --> 00:17:33,126
to the wall in less than a minute, moreover in the dark.

355
00:17:33,126 --> 00:17:34,626
In addition to pass it around to his accomplices

356
00:17:34,626 --> 00:17:35,826
without using any light at all.

357
00:17:35,826 --> 00:17:36,926
Then, without even giving a signal,

358
00:17:36,926 --> 00:17:38,826
have everyone insert and turn the key at the same time.

359
00:17:38,826 --> 00:17:41,726
And finally make the treasure vanish as if by magic,

360
00:17:41,726 --> 00:17:44,226
I wonder if doing something like that is possible.

361
00:17:44,226 --> 00:17:46,226
Besides, it's even dubious

362
00:17:46,226 --> 00:17:48,626
that Thief Kid had any accomplices with him.

363
00:17:48,626 --> 00:17:51,926
If he brought that many accomplices to a closed up place like this,

364
00:17:51,926 --> 00:17:55,626
it's very likely that at least one of them would be caught.

365
00:17:55,626 --> 00:17:58,826
I would avoid any such risk at all cost.

366
00:17:58,826 --> 00:18:00,626
No good.

367
00:18:00,626 --> 00:18:03,226
I'm not good at things like this after all.

368
00:18:03,226 --> 00:18:06,426
I'm sure that this is what you'd say.

369
00:18:06,426 --> 00:18:08,526
"You can't even figure out something as simple as that?"

370
00:18:08,526 --> 00:18:11,626
Or, something to that effect.

371
00:18:11,626 --> 00:18:12,626
You'd probably keep on going at it like a sparrow,

372
00:18:12,626 --> 00:18:14,026
tweet-tweeting on forever,

373
00:18:14,026 --> 00:18:16,426
lining all your know-it-all knowledge.

374
00:18:16,426 --> 00:18:17,626
Sparrow...

375
00:18:19,726 --> 00:18:24,826
Maybe the "sparrow" is some kind of hint to that phrase.

376
00:18:24,826 --> 00:18:26,926
Why?

377
00:18:26,926 --> 00:18:29,326
It's almost completely erased,

378
00:18:29,326 --> 00:18:30,826
but the word "sparrow"

379
00:18:30,826 --> 00:18:33,326
was carved on that red pedestal.

380
00:18:33,326 --> 00:18:35,426
No joke.

381
00:18:35,426 --> 00:18:37,626
Red sparrow...

382
00:18:37,626 --> 00:18:38,726
"Vermilion Bird".

383
00:18:44,826 --> 00:18:48,826
It's true. The word "sparrow" can be seen.

384
00:18:48,826 --> 00:18:53,026
Then, maybe there was a statue of a sparrow here.

385
00:18:53,026 --> 00:18:55,226
It's not sparrow.

386
00:18:55,226 --> 00:18:57,326
Red is the vermilion color.

387
00:18:57,326 --> 00:18:59,526
If the character written on top of the character sparrow

388
00:18:59,526 --> 00:19:01,226
had been erase is the character "Zhu"

389
00:19:01,226 --> 00:19:02,926
that symbolizes the vermilion color.

390
00:19:02,926 --> 00:19:04,626
It is the legendary deity,

391
00:19:04,626 --> 00:19:06,826
one of the four gods is the Vermilion Bird.

392
00:19:06,826 --> 00:19:09,026
"Vermilion Bird"

393
00:19:09,026 --> 00:19:10,626
The vermilion bird is...

394
00:19:10,626 --> 00:19:12,826
The one that comes out a lot in games.

395
00:19:12,826 --> 00:19:15,226
The red bird that looks like the Phoenix.

396
00:19:15,226 --> 00:19:18,726
Yes. And the white pedestal

397
00:19:18,726 --> 00:19:21,426
to the right of the red pedestal facing it,

398
00:19:21,426 --> 00:19:22,726
is the White Tiger.

399
00:19:22,726 --> 00:19:25,926
"White Tiger"

400
00:19:25,926 --> 00:19:29,026
The black pedestal to its right on the side is...

401
00:19:29,026 --> 00:19:30,626
the Black Tortoise.

402
00:19:30,626 --> 00:19:32,526
"Black Tortoise"

403
00:19:33,526 --> 00:19:35,226
And the one to the right on the side,

404
00:19:35,226 --> 00:19:36,826
that is to the left of the first red pedestal,

405
00:19:36,826 --> 00:19:40,326
on top of the green pedestal,

406
00:19:40,326 --> 00:19:42,826
it may be safe and correct to say

407
00:19:42,826 --> 00:19:44,526
that the statue of the Blue Dragon was there.

408
00:19:44,526 --> 00:19:46,126
Please wait.

409
00:19:46,126 --> 00:19:49,226
It's called the Blue Dragon, isn't it?

410
00:19:49,226 --> 00:19:51,926
But, the color of the pedestal is green.

411
00:19:51,926 --> 00:19:53,226
The word "green"

412
00:19:53,226 --> 00:19:54,826
originally referred to the lush green

413
00:19:54,826 --> 00:19:57,826
tree-line mountains, green trees and plants.

414
00:19:57,826 --> 00:20:02,226
The true color of the dragon is said to be green.

415
00:20:02,226 --> 00:20:06,826
The four deities each protect a certain direction,

416
00:20:06,826 --> 00:20:08,326
The Vermilion Bird is the guardian of the South.

417
00:20:08,326 --> 00:20:09,926
The White Tiger guards the West.

418
00:20:09,926 --> 00:20:11,526
The Black Tortoise guards the North.

419
00:20:11,526 --> 00:20:13,226
And, the Blue Dragon, the East.

420
00:20:13,226 --> 00:20:16,526
And the one that is positioned in the middle is...

421
00:20:16,526 --> 00:20:18,126
this giraffe.

422
00:20:19,726 --> 00:20:22,926
So, the sentence that was written by Kichiemon Samizu

423
00:20:22,926 --> 00:20:25,426
at the foot of the pillar means...

424
00:20:25,426 --> 00:20:30,426
Well, it's a sort of after-care for in case

425
00:20:30,426 --> 00:20:33,226
at a later time, the keys are lost or stolen.

426
00:20:33,226 --> 00:20:36,226
The first part, "One who desires to acquire the giraffe

427
00:20:36,226 --> 00:20:37,826
without using the correct method" means...

428
00:20:37,826 --> 00:20:39,526
Anyone who wants to get a hold of the giraffe's horn

429
00:20:39,526 --> 00:20:41,126
without relying on the keys.

430
00:20:41,126 --> 00:20:45,726
That follows behind means

431
00:20:45,726 --> 00:20:49,826
the flow of the moving of places and time.

432
00:20:49,826 --> 00:20:52,126
In other words, it can also be interpreted

433
00:20:52,126 --> 00:20:56,426
as to let things just be, but...

434
00:20:56,426 --> 00:20:58,526
So, if we stay here and do nothing,

435
00:20:58,526 --> 00:21:00,926
is the giraffe going to come out of the pillar?

436
00:21:00,926 --> 00:21:02,126
No.

437
00:21:02,126 --> 00:21:04,026
If the four pedestals that are placed in the four corners

438
00:21:04,026 --> 00:21:05,726
of this room each stand for the Vermilion Bird,

439
00:21:05,726 --> 00:21:08,526
White Tiger, Black Tortoise and Blue Dragon

440
00:21:08,526 --> 00:21:09,926
it may have something to do

441
00:21:09,926 --> 00:21:11,426
with the color each deity symbolizes,

442
00:21:11,426 --> 00:21:13,626
as well as the direction.

443
00:21:13,626 --> 00:21:16,026
Right. I think we're suppose to do something

444
00:21:16,026 --> 00:21:17,426
to keep in the flow of the four pedestals

445
00:21:17,426 --> 00:21:19,226
by doing something in a given order.

446
00:21:19,226 --> 00:21:21,526
There is no order to the color.

447
00:21:21,526 --> 00:21:23,626
Maybe we're supposed to do something

448
00:21:23,626 --> 00:21:26,226
in the order of east, west south and north?

449
00:21:26,226 --> 00:21:29,626
But, they have the "east-north".

450
00:21:29,626 --> 00:21:30,626
Northeast district too.

451
00:21:30,626 --> 00:21:32,026
Isn't the direction next to east supposed to be north?

452
00:21:32,026 --> 00:21:34,326
I think north comes first.

453
00:21:34,326 --> 00:21:37,826
Because north is located at the very top on every map.

454
00:21:37,826 --> 00:21:39,926
I guess just the direction won't help us in figuring out

455
00:21:39,926 --> 00:21:41,626
what order something should be done.

456
00:21:41,626 --> 00:21:43,826
Be it clockwise or counter clockwise,

457
00:21:43,826 --> 00:21:45,726
the flow is the flow.

458
00:21:45,726 --> 00:21:48,226
True. I hope there is some kind of set order

459
00:21:48,226 --> 00:21:50,026
to the Vermilion Bird, White Tiger,

460
00:21:50,026 --> 00:21:52,826
Black Tortoise and Blue Dragon.

461
00:21:52,826 --> 00:21:55,626
If it were Conan, he may know something.

462
00:21:55,626 --> 00:21:58,626
He's been asleep for a while now.

463
00:21:58,626 --> 00:21:59,626
At any rate,

464
00:21:59,626 --> 00:22:02,726
in order to make the giraffe appear from out of this pillar,

465
00:22:02,726 --> 00:22:04,526
we've got no choice but to insert keys into the keyholes

466
00:22:04,526 --> 00:22:07,426
of the four pedestals and turn them at the same time

467
00:22:07,426 --> 00:22:08,626
or without using the keys,

468
00:22:08,626 --> 00:22:12,226
do something to the four pedestals in a certain order.

469
00:22:12,226 --> 00:22:14,226
There is no other possible way to do it.

470
00:22:14,226 --> 00:22:16,826
It would be impossible for Thief Kid alone to do something like that

471
00:22:16,826 --> 00:22:20,026
within the one minute of the time the place blacked out.

472
00:22:20,026 --> 00:22:21,426
If he had any accomplices,

473
00:22:21,426 --> 00:22:24,326
he would've had to give out some kind of signal.

474
00:22:24,326 --> 00:22:26,526
Let's check on that, first of all.

475
00:22:26,526 --> 00:22:29,126
Check on it, how?

476
00:22:29,126 --> 00:22:30,526
They're here, aren't they?

477
00:22:30,526 --> 00:22:34,726
The TV crew that is taking evidence

478
00:22:34,726 --> 00:22:37,926
filled VTR shots.

479
00:22:37,926 --> 00:22:41,726
Conan, I guess we have no choice

480
00:22:41,726 --> 00:22:43,126
but to do what we can

481
00:22:43,126 --> 00:22:45,726
on our own until you wake up.

482
00:24:07,126 --> 00:24:10,526
Young staff were supposed to come today.

483
00:24:10,526 --> 00:24:12,026
If you put it that way,

484
00:24:12,026 --> 00:24:14,926
you, the cameraman is also suspicious!

485
00:24:14,926 --> 00:24:17,826
Don't just sleep there forever,

486
00:24:17,826 --> 00:24:19,126
and help us figure this out, will you?

487
00:24:19,126 --> 00:24:20,126
White.

488
00:24:20,126 --> 00:24:21,726
What?

489
00:24:21,726 --> 00:24:27,126
Hurry up and unlock that door.

490
00:24:27,126 --> 00:24:29,026
You're the one, aren't you?

491
00:24:29,026 --> 00:24:31,426
The magician under the moon.

492
00:24:31,426 --> 00:24:32,926
Next Conan,

493
00:24:32,926 --> 00:24:36,225
"Thief Kid vs. the Detective Squad"

494
00:24:51,787 --> 00:24:53,787
Next Conan's Hint:

495
00:24:53,787 --> 00:24:56,487
"Genta's 10 yen size baldness"

496
00:24:56,487 --> 00:24:58,887
There are times when Genta leads us to clues too.

497
00:24:58,887 --> 00:25:00,387
That sure is a bald "bold" remark.

